[Name] FreeImage (+ FreeImagePlus)
[Summary] FreeImage is a library to support popular graphics image formats.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL) and the FreeImage Public License (FIPL)
[Description] FreeImage is an Open Source library project for 
developers who would like to support popular graphics image formats 
like PNG, BMP, JPEG, TIFF and others as needed by today's 
multimedia applications. FreeImage is easy to use, fast, 
multithreading safe, compatible with all 32-bit versions of Windows,
and cross-platform (works both with Linux and Mac OS X).
This version includes FreeImagePlus, a wrapper for C++.
[Homepage] http://freeimage.sourceforge.net/
